description:
## Context
`MatchingFlowService.AcceptPairRequestAsync` (line 108, `Service/MatchingFlowService.cs`) has a TOCTOU race: reads mentor capacity, then creates the pair in two separate non-atomic calls. Two supervisors accepting simultaneously could over-assign a mentor. The `Pairs` and `PairRequests` EF entities have xmin tokens.

## Goal
Wrap the capacity-check + pair-creation in a single `RepeatableRead` transaction. Use `GetByIdAsync` (added to `IPairRequestRepo` in issue #3) instead of the current loop over all mentors.

## AI Agent Prompt
Open `Service/MatchingFlowService.cs`:

1. Inject `MentoringDbContext` into the constructor and update the DI registration in `Service/DI/ServiceDependencyInjection.cs`.
2. Replace the loop at lines 112–121 with `await _pairRequestRepo.GetByIdAsync(requestId)`.
3. Wrap the method body in:
```csharp
using var tx = await _context.Database.BeginTransactionAsync(IsolationLevel.RepeatableRead);
try
{
    // ... body ...
    await tx.CommitAsync();
    return Result.Ok();
}
catch (DbUpdateConcurrencyException)
{
    await tx.RollbackAsync();
    return Result.Failure("This request was modified by someone else. Please refresh and try again.");
}
catch { await tx.RollbackAsync(); throw; }
```
4. Re-read the `PairRequest` from the DB inside the transaction (so the xmin token is attached before the update call).

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] No more loop over all mentors to find a request by ID
- [ ] Concurrent acceptance of the same request returns `Result.Failure` with a clear message
- [ ] `dotnet build MentoringApp.sln` passes
